When humans are happy,

178
00:11:55,414 --> 00:11:57,416
don't they all like to eat something sweet?

179
00:11:58,350 --> 00:12:01,687
At the right time, in the right place,

180
00:12:01,687 --> 00:12:03,222
and with the right person.

181
00:12:04,623 --> 00:12:07,159
Through your eyes, my world

182
00:12:07,159 --> 00:12:09,161
seems a bit more meaningful.

183
00:12:12,164 --> 00:12:14,433
Do you like your life, Master?

184
00:12:15,634 --> 00:12:17,470
It doesn't matter whether I like it or not.

185
00:12:20,673 --> 00:12:22,308
What about you?

186
00:12:22,308 --> 00:12:24,043
Do you like your life?

187
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:28,514
It doesn't matter whether I like it or not.

188
00:12:32,384 --> 00:12:34,353
My life from my birth to the age of 80

189
00:12:34,353 --> 00:12:36,856
was constructed in a database.

190
00:12:36,856 --> 00:12:39,358
Those settings are all very vague.

191
00:12:39,358 --> 00:12:41,727
That's why I envy your lives.

192
00:12:42,328 --> 00:12:44,597
But I know that's not right.

193
00:12:45,197 --> 00:12:47,900
In the beautifully literary terms of humanity,

194
00:12:48,467 --> 00:12:49,902
it's a luxury.

195
00:12:51,804 --> 00:12:54,907
What will you be doing when you're 80?

196
00:12:57,176 --> 00:13:00,412
The system's design is very traditional.

197
00:13:01,247 --> 00:13:03,182
It's probably a scene like that.

198
00:13:05,684 --> 00:13:07,253
With company.

199
00:13:07,253 --> 00:13:09,255
What does he look like?

200
00:13:10,823 --> 00:13:13,659
It doesn't matter what he looks like.

201
00:13:13,659 --> 00:13:15,494
After all, it's all virtual.

202
00:13:23,569 --> 00:13:25,371
You once said

203
00:13:25,371 --> 00:13:28,808
that everything we've gone through
has created the present,

204
00:13:29,575 --> 00:13:31,443
and then accumulated to become me.

205
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:34,079
So I consider myself very fortunate

206
00:13:34,079 --> 00:13:36,081
to be by your side.

207
00:13:37,283 --> 00:13:39,118
If after a long, long time,

208
00:13:39,118 --> 00:13:41,453
the person by your side is still me,

209
00:13:41,453 --> 00:13:43,689
that would be even better.

210
00:13:43,689 --> 00:13:45,558
We could grow old together.

211
00:13:48,027 --> 00:13:50,529
But my appearance can't age.

212
00:13:51,163 --> 00:13:53,899
Wouldn't we look strange when the time comes?

213
00:13:54,433 --> 00:13:56,802
I don't know if Boss will solve it for us.

214
00:13:58,771 --> 00:14:01,173
But if we have to change the shell,

215
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:02,942
wouldn't that be expensive?

216
00:14:05,778 --> 00:14:07,379
What should we do then?

217
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:12,918
Do you have any wishes?

218
00:14:14,153 --> 00:14:15,360
Wishes?

219
00:14:16,388 --> 00:14:18,557
What wishes do you have? Tell me.

220
00:14:18,557 --> 00:14:20,292
Let's fulfill them together.

221
00:14:22,127 --> 00:14:25,064
My wish is to fulfill your wishes.

222
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:27,299
You are an independent entity.

223
00:14:27,299 --> 00:14:29,501
You can also have your own wishes.

224
00:14:30,336 --> 00:14:33,239
None of us own anyone.

225
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:36,775
So, you should care more about yourself.

226
00:14:38,177 --> 00:14:40,846
Isn't it a bug

227
00:14:40,846 --> 00:14:43,449
to make choices

228
00:14:43,449 --> 00:14:45,284
following one's consciousness?

229
00:14:47,319 --> 00:14:48,520
Human emotions

230
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:51,156
do not belong to any string
of numbers or coding.

231
00:14:51,156 --> 00:14:53,392
And the way this world operates

232
00:14:53,392 --> 00:14:55,728
never has a correct answer to begin with.

233
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:58,731
So you don't have to live
according to the original settings.

234
00:15:02,434 --> 00:15:04,236
Can I really do that?

235
00:15:21,453 --> 00:15:23,489
Do you have any place in mind you'd like to go?

236
00:15:26,158 --> 00:15:28,127
I want to go to the riverbank.

237
00:15:28,127 --> 00:15:29,628
The riverbank?

238
00:15:30,396 --> 00:15:32,698
Okay, I'll look it up.

239
00:15:47,413 --> 00:15:50,249
Your wish is to come here.

240
00:15:50,249 --> 00:15:51,884
I've always been curious.

241
00:15:52,885 --> 00:15:57,022
Although this place is dark, smelly,
infested with mosquitoes,

242
00:15:57,723 --> 00:15:59,458
and full of various dangers,

243
00:16:19,211 --> 00:16:21,647
and the behavior of couples

244
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:23,382
has no value whatsoever,

245
00:16:23,949 --> 00:16:26,118
why does everyone still enjoy it tirelessly?

246
00:16:27,386 --> 00:16:29,755
That might be because

247
00:16:29,755 --> 00:16:31,924
you don't have much experience with love.

248
00:16:36,195 --> 00:16:37,229
Come on.

249
00:16:37,229 --> 00:16:38,931
Consider it a return for your care.

250
00:16:38,931 --> 00:16:41,233
Hold hands, and feel it.

251
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:53,879
How is it?

252
00:16:53,879 --> 00:16:55,647
Do you feel anything different?

253
00:16:56,382 --> 00:17:00,219
The way you hold hands
is like an adult holding a child's hand.

254
00:17:00,919 --> 00:17:02,988
It lacks a romantic touch.

255
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:05,090
It should be like this.

256
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:18,570
Although you're not used
to someone holding your hand,

257
00:17:18,570 --> 00:17:20,839
I hope that when I'm with you,

258
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:22,841
we can keep holding hands.

259
00:17:27,279 --> 00:17:28,781
Let's go.

260
00:17:33,264 --> 00:17:38,128
♫ I hide in yesterday
where there's no fuss or noise ♫

