00:19:55,427 --> 00:19:56,995
What era are we in?

277
00:19:56,995 --> 00:19:58,697
I thought you'd send your wish list

278
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,699
via a message.

279
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:03,135
This is called a sense of ceremony.

280
00:20:03,835 --> 00:20:07,506
And it feels more personal this way.

281
00:20:10,275 --> 00:20:12,044
Is printing out photos the same?

282
00:20:14,012 --> 00:20:16,882
I've seen the photo frames in your room.

283
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:20,152
You were smiling so happily in them,

284
00:20:20,152 --> 00:20:22,154
just like you are now.

285
00:20:25,524 --> 00:20:29,761
Don't humans always care
about the sense of ceremony?

286
00:20:29,761 --> 00:20:31,597
Don't you?

287
00:20:32,864 --> 00:20:35,334
I'm curious about what's in your head.

288
00:20:38,971 --> 00:20:42,174
Einstein said that emotions and desires

289
00:20:42,174 --> 00:20:44,109
are the driving force

290
00:20:44,109 --> 00:20:45,744
behind all human efforts and creation.

291
00:20:46,345 --> 00:20:47,746
In this definition,

292
00:20:47,746 --> 00:20:49,681
Heng 9 with desires

293
00:20:49,681 --> 00:20:51,683
is more human-like than I am.

294
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,772
You can't give me away to someone else.

295
00:20:56,772 --> 00:20:59,558
You know, I will only have you in here.

296
00:20:59,558 --> 00:21:00,726
There won't be anyone else.

297
00:21:00,726 --> 00:21:03,061
Since you've chosen to wear this to swim today,

298
00:21:03,061 --> 00:21:04,224
you might as well skip eating.

299
00:21:04,224 --> 00:21:05,314
You'll gain weight.

300
00:21:05,314 --> 00:21:07,532
If life just stops here forever,

301
00:21:07,532 --> 00:21:08,734
that would also be fine.

302
00:21:19,126 --> 00:21:26,270
♫ Turns out that a long time is not forever ♫

303
00:21:26,270 --> 00:21:28,862
♫ A hand held for so long ♫

304
00:21:28,862 --> 00:21:32,904
♫ Has become a hand waving goodbye ♫

305
00:21:32,904 --> 00:21:38,078
♫ The promises so bravely
voiced at the beginning ♫

306
00:21:38,078 --> 00:21:42,166
♫ Have now lost the reason to be fulfilled ♫

307
00:21:42,166 --> 00:21:43,902
♫ A beginning with no end ♫

308
00:21:43,902 --> 00:21:48,222
♫ If we must pursue who's at fault ♫

309
00:21:48,222 --> 00:21:53,941
♫ Blame it all on me ♫

310
00:21:53,941 --> 00:21:57,822
♫ Since words of love are spoken
without a second thought ♫

311
00:21:57,822 --> 00:22:01,882
♫ Why can't I let go with ease ♫

312
00:22:01,882 --> 00:22:08,414
[AntiReset]
♫ Some loss is called gaining ♫
